Language name: EVEN
Language number: 2167
Alternate names: Lamut
Classification: Ural-Altaic, Tungus
Comments: Even is spoken in the Yakut ASSR and the 
Kamchatka Peninsula of the USSR and along the Okhotsk 
Artic coast. All simple vowels can appear long.  Low vowel 
/a_/ is grouped with the pharyngealized vowels to form one 
set of harmonizing vowels.  /k/ is uvular before this set 
of vowels.

Sources: 

Novikova, K.A. 1960. Ocherki dialektov Evenskogo Jazyka: 
Ol'skij Govor 1. Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Moscow 
and Leningrad.